						<div class="postbody">Both multicarts with Nintendo World Cup (the US one with Super Spike V'Ball and the PAL one with SMB1 and Tetris) likewise put the mapper register in $6000.
<br />
<br /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">What I'm not sure is how to boot to the menu.</div>
<br />Google power-on reset, and make sure the menu's bank number gets loaded.
<br />
<br />I think we can do this with a 74HC161, a couple quad NANDs (74HC00), and some sort of POR circuit to generate a pulse on the 161's CLEAR input. I'd recommend against the sort of POR in the NES-EVENT board, which depends on a signal not present in toploaders.</div>

